# IoT-Based Pest Alerting System Using Raspberry Pi 4B

## Overview

The IoT-Based Pest Alerting System is a smart agriculture solution developed using Raspberry Pi 4B+, IoT sensors, Artificial Intelligence, and Computer Vision technologies.

The system continuously monitors environmental conditions such as temperature, humidity, soil moisture, and rainfall while simultaneously detecting pests using a camera and AI-based image processing.

When pests are detected, the system automatically sends email alerts to farmers and updates a web dashboard for remote monitoring.

---

## Features

* Real-time Pest Detection

* Temperature Monitoring

* Humidity Monitoring

* Soil Moisture Monitoring

* Rainfall Detection

* Email Alert Notifications

* Flask Web Dashboard

* Cloud-Based Monitoring

* Raspberry Pi Edge Computing

---

## Hardware Components

* Raspberry Pi 4B+

* DHT11 Temperature and Humidity Sensor

* YL-69 Soil Moisture Sensor

* YL-83 Rain Sensor

* Logitech USB Camera

* Wi-Fi Module (On-board)

---

## Software Used

* Python

* Flask

* OpenCV

* Azure Custom Vision

* Raspberry Pi OS

* Thonny IDE

---

## System Architecture

Sensors + Camera → Raspberry Pi 4B+ → AI Pest Detection → Cloud Storage → Email Alert → Farmer Dashboard

---

## Applications

* Smart Agriculture

* Pest Monitoring

* Precision Farming

* Crop Health Monitoring

* Automated Farm Management

---

